// (#331 L2b) A field-extract aliased free: `let y = obj.data` binds `y` to `obj`'s non-scalar
// interior buffer, so freeing `obj` dangles `y`. The spine's capture sweep marks the base of a
// non-scalar field extraction `us = shared`, so the affine `mem::free` guard REJECTS it. Closes the
// field-extract launder class (option b). Compile-reject on both engines (EXPECT_COMPILE_FAIL).
use fe

(fe::run()) to i32
